---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Daemon Core" description="The deterministic foundation beneath multi-agent intelligence.">
  <section class="hero">
    <h1>Daemon Core</h1>
    <p class="hero-tagline">The deterministic foundation beneath multi-agent intelligence.</p>
    <p class="hero-description">
      Daemon Core orchestrates reasoning, distributes workloads, and refracts intent
      through a crystalline mesh of agents. Intelligence emerges from impeccable order.
    </p>
    <p class="hero-description">
      Not an application. Not an assistant. The structural layer that enables
      multi-agent systems to operate with precision and clarity.
    </p>
    <div class="hero-cta">
      <a href="/daemon" class="btn-primary">Initialize Kernel</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2 class="section-title">Architecture</h2>
    <p class="section-intro">
      Every component reflects structured, predictable architecture.
      Intelligence arises from order. Stability emerges from constraint.
    </p>
    <div class="grid grid-3">
      <div class="feature">
        <h3>Deterministic</h3>
        <p>
          Every line, corner, and behavior reflects a structured, predictable
          architecture. Same inputs produce same outputs.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature">
        <h3>Orchestrated</h3>
        <p>
          Workloads distribute through a crystalline mesh. Agents coordinate
          without collision. Intent refracts cleanly.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature">
        <h3>Foundational</h3>
        <p>
          Other systems build atop Daemon Core. It provides the substrate
          for multi-agent computation.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2 class="section-title">System Components</h2>
    <p class="section-intro">
      The Daemon Core ecosystem comprises modular subsystems.
      Each operates independently. Together, they form the foundation.
    </p>
    <div class="grid grid-3">
      <a href="/daemon" class="card card-interactive">
        <h3>Kernel</h3>
        <p>
          The core orchestration layer. Boot sequences, safety scaling,
          vendor isolation, and multi-agent coordination.
        </p>
        <span class="badge badge-active">Active</span>
      </a>
      <div class="card coming-soon">
        <h3>SDK</h3>
        <p>
          Developer tooling for constructing Daemon Core-native agents
          and integrations.
        </p>
        <span class="badge">Pending</span>
      </div>
      <div class="card coming-soon">
        <h3>Hub</h3>
        <p>
          Central registry for agents, profiles, and shared configurations
          across deployments.
        </p>
        <span class="badge">Pending</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="status">
    <h2>Status</h2>
    <p>
      Kernel specification stabilising. Core boot protocol and safety framework defined.
      System under active development.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
